{"id":"nebuchadrezzar","term":"Nebuchadrezzar","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>=Nebuchadnezzar (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 21:2\">Jer. 21:2</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:7\">7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 23:1\">22:25</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 24:1\">24:1</a>, etc.), a nearer approach to the correct spelling of the word.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Jeremiah 21:2","Genesis 1:7","Genesis 23:1","Genesis 24:1"]}